            "body": ">Actually when I try to use these commands it just splits my window in two here but it doesn't let me debug the code...\r\n\r\nAh, yes, the autocommand needs to allow nested autocommmands, e.g. `:au BufWrite file.js ++nested sp term://node inspect %`.\r\n\r\n>But set makeprg=node\\ inspect\\ % | set autowrite | make works fine for doing interactively on Vim...\r\n\r\nYes, Vim and Neovim differ on interactivity of commands ran through bang/system/make :).",
